# OpenLayers Mapping Patterns

## Core Approach

- Store map instances in refs, never state (prevents re-renders)
- Always implement cleanup in useEffect returns
- Handle coordinate transformations explicitly (EPSG:4326 ↔ EPSG:3857)

## Reference Implementations

- **Main Map Component**: `src/components/DatasetMap/DatasetMap.tsx`

  - Shows proper map initialization and cleanup
  - Layer management with refs
  - Event handling patterns

- **Details Map**: `src/components/DatasetDetailsMap/DatasetDetailsMap.tsx`

  - WebGL layers for raster data (GeoTIFF/COG)
  - Vector tile integration
  - Viewport synchronization

- **Audit Map**: `src/components/DatasetAudit/DatasetAuditMap.tsx`
  - Drawing interactions
  - Feature modification
  - AOI (Area of Interest) handling

## Key Patterns to Follow

- Use `mapRef.current` pattern from DatasetMap.tsx
- Layer disposal pattern from DatasetDetailsMap cleanup
- Coordinate transformation utilities in `src/utils/parseBBox.tsx`
- Event cleanup patterns in all map components
- Dispose layers and sources in useEffect cleanup

## Avoid

- Storing OpenLayers objects in React state
- Creating new map instances on every render
- Forgetting to dispose layers and sources
